82
00:03:06.940 --> 00:03:09.400
'It has to do with bubbles,' says Schallhorn. 

83
00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:12.740
'The way bubbles form and interact inside the chamber 

84
00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:15.760
is surprising-and not predicted by our models. 

85
00:03:15.780 --> 00:03:18.180
We were taken off guard with what we saw in the data.'

86
00:03:18.200 --> 00:03:21.300
The bubbling and frothing of shaken fuels 

87
00:03:21.320 --> 00:03:23.850
is cutting-edge research in fluid dynamics, 

88
00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:27.320
and SPHERE-Slosh is showing that it may be very important.  

89
